    <sect1 id="introduction" status="draft">
        <title>Introduction</title>
        <para>The &app; is a graphical frontend to the <application>APT</application> package
            management system for the K Desktop Environment (KDE). Modeled along the lines of
                <application>Kapture</application>, another graphical interface developed for KDE,
            &appshort; provides an easy-to-use and familiar interface with which users can
            perform software management operations.</para>
        <para>&appshort; can be started from the K menu system or the command line. In order to
            start &appshort; you will be required to provide your password.</para>
        <para>To start &appshort; from the menu system select <menuchoice>
                <guimenu>K Menu</guimenu>
                <guisubmenu>System</guisubmenu>
                <guimenuitem>Adept (Package Manager)</guimenuitem>
            </menuchoice>. </para>
        <para>To start &appshort; from the command line:</para>
        <programlisting>
                sudo adept
                </programlisting>
        <para>Both methods require that you enter your password. This will run &appshort; with
            root privileges which will be required in order to perform the requested operations. It
            is therefore advised that you use &appshort; with caution since improper usage could
            lead to the removal, deletion, or corruption of software packages that are required to
            preserve system integrity.</para>
    </sect1>
    <sect1 id="get-started" status="draft">
        <title>Getting Started</title>
        <para>On startup, &appshort; will build the dependency tree for all installed software
            packages and then display the main window.</para>
        <figure id="main-window">
            <title>Main Window</title>
            <screenshot>
                <mediaobject>
                    <imageobject>
                        <imagedata fileref="figures/C/adept.png" format="PNG"/>
                    </imageobject>
                    <caption>Adept: Main Window</caption>
                </mediaobject>
            </screenshot>
        </figure>
        <para>The main window is comprised of the following regions:</para>
        <itemizedlist>
            <listitem>
                <para>
                    <xref linkend="adept-menus" endterm="title-adept-menus"/>
                </para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>
                    <xref linkend="adept-toolbar" endterm="title-adept-toolbar"/>
                </para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>
                    <xref linkend="adept-filters" endterm="title-adept-filters"/>
                </para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>
                    <xref linkend="adept-list" endterm="title-adept-list"/>
                </para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>
                    <xref linkend="adept-status" endterm="title-adept-status"/>
                </para>
            </listitem>
        </itemizedlist>
        <sect2 id="adept-menus" status="draft">
            <title id="title-adept-menus">Menu Bar</title>
            <para>The Menu Bar provides the following menus and options:</para>
            <variablelist>
                <varlistentry>
                    <term>Adept</term>
                    <listitem>
                        <itemizedlist>
                            <listitem>
                                <para>
                                    <emphasis>Fetch Updates</emphasis>: Reload the list of packages
                                    from known software repositories.</para>
                            </listitem>
                            <listitem>
                                <para>
                                    <emphasis>Manage Repositories</emphasis>: View/manage the list
                                    of known software repositories.</para>
                            </listitem>
                            <listitem>
                                <para>
                                    <emphasis>Commit Changes</emphasis>: Apply changes (i.e.
                                    install, remove, upgrade) that have been marked since the last
                                    Commit Changes operation.</para>
                            </listitem>
                            <listitem>
                                <para>
                                    <emphasis>Safe Upgrade</emphasis>: Mark the equivalent of the
                                        <emphasis>APT</emphasis> command
                                    <emphasis>upgrade</emphasis>.</para>
                            </listitem>
                            <listitem>
                                <para>
                                    <emphasis>Full Upgrade</emphasis>: Mark the equivalent of the
                                        <emphasis>APT</emphasis> command
                                    <emphasis>dist-upgrade</emphasis>.</para>
                            </listitem>
                            <listitem>
                                <para>
                                    <emphasis>Quit</emphasis>: Terminate the application.</para>
                            </listitem>
                        </itemizedlist>
                    </listitem>
                </varlistentry>
                <varlistentry>
                    <term>Edit</term>
                    <listitem>
                        <itemizedlist>
                            <listitem>
                                <para>
                                    <emphasis>Undo</emphasis>: Undo the last action (this will not
                                    undo a <emphasis>Commit Changes</emphasis> action).</para>
                            </listitem>
                            <listitem>
                                <para>
                                    <emphasis>Redo</emphasis>: Redo the last 'undone'
                                action.</para>
                            </listitem>
                        </itemizedlist>
                    </listitem>
                </varlistentry>
                <varlistentry>
                    <term>Settings</term>
                    <listitem>
                        <itemizedlist>
                            <listitem>
                                <para>
                                    <emphasis>Hide Toolbar</emphasis>: Hide the icon-based
                                toolbar.</para>
                            </listitem>
                            <listitem>
                                <para>
                                    <emphasis>Hide Statusbar</emphasis>: Hide the statusbar located
                                    at the bottom of the window.</para>
                            </listitem>
                            <listitem>
                                <para>
                                    <emphasis>Configure Shortcuts...</emphasis>: Configure keyboard
                                    shortcuts for common actions.</para>
                            </listitem>
                            <listitem>
                                <para>
                                    <emphasis>Configure Toolbars...</emphasis>: Configure the layout
                                    and actions represented in the icon-based toolbar.</para>
                            </listitem>
                        </itemizedlist>
                    </listitem>
                </varlistentry>
                <varlistentry>
                    <term>Help</term>
                    <listitem>
                        <itemizedlist>
                            <listitem>
                                <para>
                                    <emphasis>Adept Manager Handbook</emphasis>: This
                                document.</para>
                            </listitem>
                            <listitem>
                                <para>
                                    <emphasis>What's This?</emphasis>: Context-sensitive help for
                                    this applicaiton.</para>
                            </listitem>
                            <listitem>
                                <para>
                                    <emphasis>Report Bug...</emphasis>: Report a bug to the
                                    KDE-based Bugzilla repository.</para>
                            </listitem>
                            <listitem>
                                <para>
                                    <emphasis>About Adept Manager</emphasis>: Information (i.e.
                                    version, author, etc.) about this application.</para>
                            </listitem>
                            <listitem>
                                <para>
                                    <emphasis>About KDE</emphasis>: Information (i.e. version,
                                    authors, etc.) about KDE.</para>
                            </listitem>
                        </itemizedlist>
                    </listitem>
                </varlistentry>
            </variablelist>
        </sect2>
        <sect2 id="adept-toolbar" status="draft">
            <title id="title-adept-toolbar">Toolbar</title>
            <para>The toolbar provides the following actions from left to right:<variablelist>
                    <varlistentry>
                        <term>
                            <inlinemediaobject>
                                <imageobject>
                                    <imagedata fileref="figures/C/adept_update.png" format="PNG"/>
                                </imageobject>
                            </inlinemediaobject>
                        </term>
                        <listitem>
                            <para>Reload the list of packages from known software repositories.
                            </para>
                        </listitem>
                    </varlistentry>
                    <varlistentry>
                        <term>
                            <inlinemediaobject>
                                <imageobject>
                                    <imagedata fileref="figures/C/adept_commit.png" format="PNG"/>
                                </imageobject>
                            </inlinemediaobject>
                        </term>
                        <listitem>
                            <para>Commit all marked changes to the system.</para>
                        </listitem>
                    </varlistentry>
                    <varlistentry>
                        <term>
                            <inlinemediaobject>
                                <imageobject>
                                    <imagedata fileref="figures/C/adept_distupgrade.png" format="PNG"
                                    />
                                </imageobject>
                            </inlinemediaobject>
                        </term>
                        <listitem>
                            <para>Mark all packages tagged as 'upgradable' for installation.</para>
                        </listitem>
                    </varlistentry>
                    <varlistentry>
                        <term>
                            <inlinemediaobject>
                                <imageobject>
                                    <imagedata fileref="figures/C/adept_preview.png" format="PNG"/>
                                </imageobject>
                            </inlinemediaobject>
                        </term>
                        <listitem>
                            <para>Preview all the changes that are marked on your system without
                                actually committing those changes.</para>
                        </listitem>
                    </varlistentry>
                    <varlistentry>
                        <term>
                            <inlinemediaobject>
                                <imageobject>
                                    <imagedata fileref="figures/C/undo.png" format="PNG"/>
                                </imageobject>
                            </inlinemediaobject>
                        </term>
                        <listitem>
                            <para>Undo the last marked change (must be done prior to commit)</para>
                        </listitem>
                    </varlistentry>
                    <varlistentry>
                        <term>
                            <inlinemediaobject>
                                <imageobject>
                                    <imagedata fileref="figures/C/redo.png" format="PNG"/>
                                </imageobject>
                            </inlinemediaobject>
                        </term>
                        <listitem>
                            <para>Redo the last marked change that was 'un-done'.</para>
                        </listitem>
                    </varlistentry>
                </variablelist>
            </para>
        </sect2>
        <sect2 id="adept-filters" status="draft">
            <title id="title-adept-filters">Active Filters</title>
            <para>The top pane is known as the Active Filters section. Comprised of drop lists, a
                dialog box and check boxes, it enables you to select categories containing
                predefined filters, or in the case of the <emphasis>Quick Filter</emphasis> dialog,
                filters you define yourself. When selected, filters serve to reduce the number of
                packages displayed in <xref linkend="adept-list" endterm="title-adept-list"/>. </para>
            <screenshot>
                <mediaobject>
                    <imageobject>
                        <imagedata fileref="figures/C/category-filters.png" format="PNG"/>
                    </imageobject>
                </mediaobject>
            </screenshot>
            <para>The following categories are available:</para>
            <itemizedlist>
                <listitem>
                    <para>
                        <xref linkend="use" endterm="title-use"/>
                    </para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>
                        <xref linkend="role" endterm="title-role"/>
                    </para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>
                        <xref linkend="interface" endterm="title-interface"/>
                    </para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>
                        <xref linkend="works-with" endterm="title-works-with"/>
                    </para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>
                        <xref linkend="quick-filter" endterm="title-quick-filter"/>
                    </para>
                </listitem>
                <listitem>
                    <para>
                        <xref linkend="state-filter" endterm="title-state-filter"/>
                    </para>
                </listitem>
            </itemizedlist>
            <sect3 id="use" status="draft">
                <title id="title-use">Use</title>
                <para>The <emphasis>Use</emphasis> Easy Tag Filter allows the filtering of packages
                    based on their usage, such as browsing, chatting or editing applications (to
                    name a very few).</para>
                <screenshot>
                    <mediaobject>
                        <imageobject>
                            <imagedata fileref="figures/C/use-filter.png" format="PNG"/>
                        </imageobject>
                        <caption>Use Easy Tag Filter</caption>
                    </mediaobject>
                </screenshot>
            </sect3>
            <sect3 id="role" status="draft">
                <title id="title-role">Role</title>
                <para>Displays a list of filters arranged by <emphasis>Role</emphasis>, such as
                    utility, source or server based packages.</para>
                <screenshot>
                    <mediaobject>
                        <imageobject>
                            <imagedata fileref="figures/C/role-filter.png" format="PNG"/>
                        </imageobject>
                        <caption>Role Easy Tag Filter</caption>
                    </mediaobject>
                </screenshot>
            </sect3>
            <sect3 id="interface" status="draft">
                <title id="title-interface">Interface</title>
                <para>Displays a list of filters related to <emphasis>Interface</emphasis>
                    characteristics. For example, web, X11 or commandline based packages.</para>
                <screenshot>
                    <mediaobject>
                        <imageobject>
                            <imagedata fileref="figures/C/interface-filter.png" format="PNG"/>
                        </imageobject>
                        <caption>Interface Easy Tag Filter</caption>
                    </mediaobject>
                </screenshot>
            </sect3>
            <sect3 id="works-with" status="draft">
                <title id="title-works-with">Works With</title>
                <para>Allows the selection of filters that define the package in terms of what it
                        <emphasis>Works With</emphasis>. These could be pacakages related to MP3,
                    images or mail.</para>
                <screenshot>
                    <mediaobject>
                        <imageobject>
                            <imagedata fileref="figures/C/works-with-filter.png" format="PNG"/>
                        </imageobject>
                        <caption>Works With Easy Tag Filter</caption>
                    </mediaobject>
                </screenshot>
            </sect3>
            <sect3 id="quick-filter" status="draft">
                <title id="title-quick-filter">Quick Filter</title>
                <para>A dialog box provided for custom filtering. This filter will search for the
                    supplied term in the name, short description or maintainer name portions of the
                    package information.</para>
                <screenshot>
                    <mediaobject>
                        <imageobject>
                            <imagedata fileref="figures/C/quick-filter.png" format="PNG"/>
                        </imageobject>
                        <caption>Quick Filter</caption>
                    </mediaobject>
                </screenshot>
            </sect3>
            <sect3 id="state-filter" status="draft">
                <title id="title-state-filter">State Filter</title>
                <para>The <emphasis>State Filter</emphasis> provides convenient and easy check boxes
                    which allow the filtering of packages by their state (i.e. Not Installed,
                    Installed, Upgradable) or marked action (i.e. Keep, Install, Remove, Upgrade).</para>
                <screenshot>
                    <mediaobject>
                        <imageobject>
                            <imagedata fileref="figures/C/state-filter.png" format="PNG"/>
                        </imageobject>
                        <caption>State Filter</caption>
                    </mediaobject>
                </screenshot>
            </sect3>
        </sect2>
        <!-- Troy Williams:  Ended editing at this point: need to put Adept screenshots in to this point. -->
        <sect2 id="adept-list" status="draft">
            <title id="title-adept-list">Package List</title>
            <para>The bottom pane is known as the Package List. Package listings are dependent on
                the criteria defined by the filters selected in <xref linkend="adept-filters"
                    endterm="title-adept-filters"/>.</para>
            <screenshot>
                <mediaobject>
                    <imageobject>
                        <imagedata fileref="figures/C/package-list.png" format="PNG"/>
                    </imageobject>
                </mediaobject>
            </screenshot>
            <para>Listed packages are displayed in tabular form. Each package is a single record and
                provides the following information about the properties of displayed packages:</para>
            <variablelist>
                <varlistentry>
                    <term>Package</term>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>The logical name of the package.</para>
                    </listitem>
                </varlistentry>
                <varlistentry>
                    <term>Status</term>
                    <listitem>
                        <para><emphasis>Not Installed</emphasis>, <emphasis>Installed</emphasis>,
                                <emphasis>Upgradable</emphasis>.</para>
                    </listitem>
                </varlistentry>
                <varlistentry>
                    <term>Action</term>
                    <listitem>
                        <para><emphasis>Keep</emphasis>, <emphasis>Install</emphasis>,
                                <emphasis>Remove</emphasis>, <emphasis>Upgrade</emphasis>.</para>
                    </listitem>
                </varlistentry>
                <varlistentry>
                    <term>Description</term>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>A short description of the function of the package.
                            <mousebutton>Left</mousebutton> clicking on a package name in the
                            Package List presents a more detailed description, as well as a button
                            that allows an action to be taken against the package (i.e. install,
                            remove, etc.).</para>
                        <screenshot>
                            <mediaobject>
                                <imageobject>
                                    <imagedata fileref="figures/C/package-list-long.png" format="PNG"/>
                                </imageobject>
                                <caption>Detailed Description and Action Availability</caption>
                            </mediaobject>
                        </screenshot>
                    </listitem>
                </varlistentry>
            </variablelist>
        </sect2>
        <sect2 id="adept-status" status="draft">
            <title id="title-adept-status">Status Bar</title>
            <para>The Status Bar, located at the bottom of the main window, will display the
                progress of operations and the current package state on the system. For example, how
                many packages are marked for installation and the total count of packages installed
                on the system.</para>
            <screenshot>
                <mediaobject>
                    <imageobject>
                        <imagedata fileref="figures/C/status-bar.png" format="PNG"/>
                    </imageobject>
                </mediaobject>
            </screenshot>
        </sect2>
    </sect1>
    <sect1 id="software-management" status="review">
        <title>Software Management</title>
        <sect2 id="reload-source-list" status="review">
            <title>Reloading Source Lists</title>
            <para>When new software sources have been added to the <application>APT</application>
                software sources list, the list of packages contained in the repository must be
                reloaded. For already existing software sources, &appshort; will already have a
                list of all software residing in a repository. This list is updated on a regular
                basis, normally once a day. Updates can be forced by clicking the <guibutton>Fetch
                    Updates</guibutton> button located on the toolbar or by selecting <menuchoice>
                    <guimenu>Adept</guimenu>
                    <guimenuitem>Fetch Updates</guimenuitem>
                </menuchoice>.</para>
            <para>During the Fetch Updates operation the status of the fetch operation for each
                software repository is shown by the <interface>Fetch Progress</interface> dialog.</para>
            <screenshot>
                <mediaobject>
                    <imageobject>
                        <imagedata fileref="figures/C/adept-fetch.png" format="PNG"/>
                    </imageobject>
                </mediaobject>
            </screenshot>
            <para>The <interface>Fetch Progress</interface> provides the following information about
                each fetch operation:</para>
            <variablelist>
                <varlistentry>
                    <term>Progress</term>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>A progress bar displaying completion in percentage for each software
                            repository package list.</para>
                    </listitem>
                </varlistentry>
                <varlistentry>
                    <term>Description</term>
                    <listitem>
                        <para>The location (URL) and repository name from which the package list was
                            reloaded.</para>
                    </listitem>
                </varlistentry>
            </variablelist>
        </sect2>
        <sect2 id="commit-changes" status="draft">
            <title>Committing Changes</title>
            <para>With &appshort;, none of the changes you have made will be applied to your
                system until you commit the changes. To commit the changes, you may either select <menuchoice>
                    <guimenu>Adept</guimenu>
                    <guisubmenu>Commit Changes</guisubmenu>
                </menuchoice> or, more simply, click the second icon option in the toolbar. If you
                have selected to install packages, it will first download all the requested packages
                and then install them accordingly. Also, packages that are selected for removal and
                upgrade will also be applied.</para>
<!-- Added by Hil freehil@gmail.com -->
<para>
Sometimes few packages require users to configure them in the installation process.
If this happens, you need to make selections in the text console within &appshort; before you can proceed to the next package installation.
Usually packages that require user configurations can be reconfigured by the following command:</para>
    <programlisting>
        sudo dpkg-reconfigure packages
    </programlisting>
            <para>After these changes have been committed, the package list will refresh to reflect
                the changes made to the system.</para>
        </sect2>
        <sect2 id="repo-mgmt" status="draft">
            <title>Managing Repositories</title>
            <para>&appshort; includes a mechanism with which to manage software repositories. To
                view and/or manage the repositories, select <menuchoice>
                    <guimenu>Adept</guimenu>
                    <guisubmenu>Manage Repositories</guisubmenu>
                </menuchoice>. To add a repository, enter the repository information into the New
                Repository dialog box and <mousebutton>left</mousebutton> click the
                <guibutton>Add</guibutton> button. <mousebutton>Left</mousebutton> click the
                    <guibutton>Apply</guibutton> button to save the changes, or
                <mousebutton>left</mousebutton> click the <guibutton>Reset</guibutton> button to
                abort the addition.</para>
            <para>In order to take advantage of the addition of new repositories, a <emphasis>Fetch
                    Updates</emphasis> must be performed after the addition.</para>
            <screenshot>
                <mediaobject>
                    <imageobject>
                        <imagedata fileref="figures/C/repo-man.png" format="PNG"/>
                    </imageobject>
                    <caption>Manage Repositories</caption>
                </mediaobject>
            </screenshot>
        </sect2>
    </sect1>
